# 5. Tool Selection

After evaluating the available platforms, the following combination was selected for the Customer Support Automation system.

## Primary Framework

CrewAI

Reason:

* Modular architecture
* Specialized agents
* Easy maintenance
* Workflow orchestration



## Primary Language Model

Groq

Reason:

* Fast response generation
* High-quality output
* Cloud scalability
* Easy integration with Python



## Secondary (Fallback) Language Model

Ollama

Reason:

* No API key required
* Completely free
* Local execution
* Works without internet connectivity



# 6. Proposed Multi-Model Architecture

The proposed architecture combines the advantages of cloud AI and local AI.

Workflow:

Customer

↓

FastAPI Backend

↓

CrewAI Multi-Agent Layer

↓

LLM Service Layer

↓

Groq (Primary)

↓

If Groq is unavailable

↓

Automatically Switch to Ollama

↓

Generate AI Response

This architecture improves reliability while reducing dependency on a single provider.



# 7. Advantages of the Selected Stack

## Fast Response

Groq provides extremely fast inference for customer conversations.

## Reliability

If Groq becomes unavailable, Ollama continues generating responses locally.

## Scalability

CrewAI allows additional agents such as Billing Agent, Inventory Agent, and Complaint Agent to be added without major architectural changes.

## Cost Effectiveness

The prototype can operate almost entirely on free tools.

## Modularity

Each component has a dedicated responsibility:

* FastAPI handles APIs
* CrewAI manages agents
* Groq generates cloud responses
* Ollama provides local fallback


# 8. Research Findings

The research demonstrates that no single platform satisfies every business requirement.

CrewAI provides excellent workflow orchestration but requires an external language model.

Groq offers outstanding cloud performance but depends on API availability and internet connectivity.

Ollama enables fully local execution but is limited by hardware resources.

Combining these technologies creates a hybrid architecture that is reliable, scalable, and suitable for both prototype development and future production deployment.



# 9. Conclusion

Based on the evaluation, a hybrid architecture consisting of CrewAI, Groq, and Ollama is recommended for Customer Support Automation.

CrewAI provides intelligent agent orchestration, Groq delivers fast cloud-based AI responses, and Ollama ensures uninterrupted service through local inference when external APIs are unavailable.

This architecture minimizes operational costs, improves system reliability, supports future scalability, and provides a strong foundation for enterprise-grade AI customer support solutions.

